						               													<description>Who will win this Halloween, a horde of candy-chasing kids or one kid-chasing ghost? Find out in Flick or Treat, a quick and colorful micro-dexterity game designed by Julio E. Nazario! Featuring custom 3D-printed pieces, a fun flick-and-roll mechanic, and a way to play using actual pieces of candy, this game just might become one of your new Halloween traditions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Flick or Treat takes around 15 minutes for 2-5 players to enjoy. One player will be the ghost, whose sole objective is to capture all of the kids. All other players play cooperatively as the kids, racing as a team to collect all of the candy before the ghost can grab them!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On their turn, each player will move their piece by pushing them with the Hallowheel. When they make contact with their target object (kid or candy) without falling over, they capture it! If the kids collect all the candy, they win! But if the ghost can capture all the kids first, the ghost wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
